Rescued People, Rescue People

Simply put, Rescue Project is an experience of the gospel surrounded by food, conversation and prayer. The Rescue Project appeals to those who have been walking with Jesus for years, as well as those for whom Jesus is only a figure in ancient history... {learn more}

First Annual Parish Picnic

We can't celebrate without you! We invite your entire family to come out and enjoy the afternoon with our family of parishes at our first annual Parish Picnic, featuring the music talents of GMA Dove Award-Nominated Catholic singer Sarah Kroger... {learn more}

Bread of Life Discourse

To help us grow deeper in love with Jesus in the Eucharist, join us each weekend before Mass leading up to the Parish Picnic to spend time before the Blessed Sacrament and bring the joys and struggles that weigh on your heart before our Heavenly Father. {learn more)

Stories of Light

We believe that God is working in our ordinary lives in extraordinary ways, and we strive to see Him in the ordinary things. Follow our Stories of Light Blog to see how God is blessing our community with His love, guidance, and grace. {read more}
